The '''Mummers''' were a criminal and [[Terrorist/Legends|terrorist]] organization active on [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

==Description==
{{Quote|Mummers, other than some of the lower grade members, are known to often use toxins in combat.|Sergeant [[Mercious Bragg|Bragg]], to a trooper|<ref name="SWG:TtCotFMCG" />}}
Named after the [[mummergy]] plant, the Mummers were a group of bootleggers who produced and traded illegal [[Alcohol/Legends|alcoholic]] beverages and [[Spice/Legends|spices]].<ref name="CDHZ" /> However, the Mummers radicalized at some point, becoming a terrorist organization.<ref name="SWG:BTttT" />

Mummers were also known to often use toxins in combat.<ref name="SWG:HLDwitmNB">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Legacy|Help Lt. Dunnels with ingredients to make Neural Boosters|Naboo}}</ref>

==History==
{{Quote|We identified the terrorists almost immediately; it was the Mummers. They never suspected that their communications were tapped, or maybe they just didn't care.|Sergeant Bragg, to a trooper|<ref name="SWG:TtCotFMCG" />}}
By the time of the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], the Mummers were considered by the [[RSF Intelligence Division]] as one of the four major criminal groups on Naboo, along with the [[Skaak Tippers]], the [[Nal Raka Criminal Empire]] and the [[Darkwalkers]].<ref name="SWG:TtCotFMCG" />

In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> the Mummers committed a [[Terrorist attack in Theed|terrorist attack]] in the capital city of [[Theed/Legends|Theed]].<ref name="SWG:HwtaotTa">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Legacy|Help with the aftermath of the Terrorist attack|Naboo}}</ref> In retaliation, their [[Mummer bunker|base]] was [[Raid on the Mummer bunker|raided]] by troopers of the [[Royal Naboo Security Forces/Legends|Royal Naboo Security Forces]] led by [[Sergeant/Legends|Sergeant]] [[Harriet Brunser|Brunser]]. The RSF troopers found a number of [[Bioweapon/Legends|biochemical weapons]] that had been cached among the many illegal items that had been stockpiled within the Mummers' base. The bunker [[Commander/Legends|commander]] [[Jaye Hawkson]] and the Mummer [[Chief Scientist/Legends|Chief Scientist]] [[Crimsol Vaighn]] were killed during the attack.<ref name="SWG:BTttT" />

After those events, the Mummers continued to use the bunker. The wanted murderer [[Hunnos Jarkey]] briefly took refuge there after he escaped the Royal Naboo Security Forces.<ref name="SWG:CtEM">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Legacy|Catch the Escaped Murderer|Naboo}}</ref> Later, [[Tanoa Vills]] dispatched a spacer to the [[Mummer Cave]], in the [[Gallo Mountains/Legends|Gallo Mountains]], in order to get an [[XJ5 circuit board]] from Mummer scientists.<ref name="SWG:GtPfaS" />

Around the same time, [[Sergeant/Legends|Sergeant]] [[Eom Nia]] ordered a young [[Cadet/Legends|cadet]] to attack the Mummer Cave as part of his [[Officer/Legends|officer]] combat training.<ref name="SWG:OM2">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Officer|Officer Mission 2|Naboo}}</ref>

